OHI-Northeast: Carbon Storage sub-goal

Compiled on Fri Nov 22 15:16:42 2019 by afflerbach

Summary

The Carbon Storage sub-goal measures the health of carbon storing marine habitats. In the Northeast, this includes Salt Marsh and Eelgrass habitats. Both of these habitats are also included in the Biodiversity - Habitats subgoal. We can use those same layers here. Both of these habitats are able to capture carbon at a near equal rate, so we dont include carbon storage weights. Instead we simply average the health of the habitats across each region to get a sense of how well this habitat service is doing.

Data Source

Eelgrass All spatial data, both current and historical eelgrass locations, were downloaded from the Northeast Ocean Data Portal.

Salt Marsh

Spatial land cover data was downloaded from this site for each state in the Northeast for the years 1996, 2001, 2006, and 2010.
